  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced background checks\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Specific Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement robust screening processes\n- Regular employee training\n- Maintaining detailed transaction records\n- Implementing risk assessment protocols\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across financial systems globally.",
